ia, Germany":"Bödefeld, Schmallenberg, Hochsauerlandkreis, North Rhine-Westphalia, Germany","Altenfeld, Winterberg, Hochsauerlandkreis, Arnsberg, Nordrhein-Westfalen, Germany":"Altenfeld, Winterberg, Hochsauerlandkreis, North Rhine-Westphalia, Germany","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Thielen","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["North German and Dutch: patronymic from   Thiel  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Thelen","meanings":["Dutch and North German: patronymic from a pet form of the ancient Germanic personal name <i>Thietilo</i>. <i>Thelen</i> is a variant of   Thielen  .","Swedish (<b>Thelén</b>): ornamental or habitational name from the element <i>Thel-</i> of uncertain meaning (see   Thelander  ) + the adjectival suffix <i>-én</i>, a derivative of Latin <i>-enius</i> ‘relating to’. Compare   Thelin  ."]},{"name":"Thiel","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Kurt, Otto, Hans, Erwin, Egon, Franz, Reinhard, Wolfgang, Angelika, Arno, Bernhard.","North German, Dutch, and Flemish: from a shortened form of the personal name <i>Thietilo</i>, an early medieval pet form of   Dietrich   (German), <i>Diederik</i> (Dutch), or from some other compound name with the same first element.","Germanized form of Sorbian, Polish, and Czech   Tyl  , a name which is (at least in part) of the same German origin as 1 above."]}]},{"name":"Gertrude","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From a Germanic female personal name, derived from <i>gār</i>, <i>gēr</i> ‘spear’ + <i>þrūþ</i> ‘strength’. The name is not found in England immediately after the Conquest, but only in the later Middle English period. It may have been introduced by migrants from the Low Countries who came to England in connection with the cloth trade, and was certainly in consistent use in some areas throughout the 16th and 17th centuries, although it was not generally popular until the 19th century, when many medieval names were revived. It has now fallen from favour again."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Gertrude Thielen was born in 1565, in Bödefeld, Schmallenberg, Hochsauerlandkreis, North Rhine-Westphalia, Germany, her father, Nicolaus Thielen, was 25 and her mother, Anna Maria Hermes, was 20. She married Hans Heinrich Hanses on 4 June 1591, in Bödefeld, Schmallenberg, Hochsauerlandkreis, North Rhine-Westphalia, Germany. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1636, in her hometown, at the age of 71."},"et":{"1565–1636":"1565–1636","1560–1636":"1560–1636","1595–1672":"1595–1672","1540–Male":"1540–Surnud","1545–1592":"1545–1592","1545":"1545","1565":"1565","1595":"1595","1540":"1540","1672":"1672","1560":"1560","1592":"1592","4 Jun 1591":"4. juuni 1591","1636":"1636","Bödefeld, Hochsauerlandkreis, Nordrhein-Westfalen, Germany":"Bödefeld, Schmallenberg, Hochsauerlandkreis, Nordrhein-Westfalen, Saksamaa","Altenfeld, Winterberg, Hochsauerlandkreis, Nordrhein-Westfalen, Deutschland":"Altenfeld, Winterberg, Hochsauerlandkreis, Nordrhein-Westfalen, Saksamaa","Bödefeld, Hochsauerlandkreis, North Rhine-Westphalia, Germany":"Bödefeld, Schmallenberg, Hochsauerlandkreis, Nordrhein-Westfalen, Saksamaa","Altenfeld, Winterberg, Hochsauerlandkreis, Arnsberg, Nordrhein-Westfalen, Germany":"Altenfeld, Winterberg, Hochsauerlandkreis, Nordrhein-Westfalen, Saksamaa"},"fi":{"1565–1636":"1565–1636","1560–1636":"1560–1636","1595–1672":"1595–1672","1540–Male":"1540–Kuollut","1545–1592":"1545–1592","1545":"1545","1565":"1565","1595":"1595","1540":"1540","1672":"1672","1560":"1560","1592":"1592","4 Jun 1591":"4. kesäkuuta 1591","1636":"1636","Bödefeld, Hochsauerlandkreis, Nordrhein-Westfalen, Germany":"Bödefeld, Schmallenberg, Hochsauerlandkreis, Nordrhein-Westfalen, Saksa","Altenfeld, Winterberg, Hochsauerlandkreis, Nordrhein-Westfalen, Deutschland":"Altenfeld, Winterberg, Hochsauerlandkreis, Nordrhein-Westfalen, Saksa","Bödefeld, Ho